  abstract: >-
    Knowledge bases in logic programming grow through fact accumulation
    but do not learn. We present DreamLog, a system that compresses its
    knowledge base through wake-sleep cycles, discovering rules that
    generalize to unseen entities. On a synthetic crafting domain with
    invented terms unknown to the LLM, compression enables 64% recall
    on unseen entities (up from 0%), with symbolic compression alone
    achieving 53%. A raw LLM baseline achieves 0%, confirming that the
    compression pipeline is genuinely necessary. On a canonical family
    tree, the full pipeline achieves 80% recall with 100% precision.
    A holdout sweep shows 100% recovery of held-out facts at up to 20%
    holdout in open-world verification mode.
